<subSubSection id="C33B07F80723A23B53D2EA0EFD454969" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9E54730723A23B53D2EA0EFEA24BB5" blockId="8.[136,1452,842,1625]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">
<emphasis id="B95588610723A23B53D2EA0EFFF54C55" bold="true" box="[136,212,842,868]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">Notes:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB029820723A23B5385EA0EFE8E4C55" author="Willdenow, C. L." box="[223,431,842,868]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" pagination="375 - 380" refId="ref4699" refString="Willdenow, C. L. (1800) Caroli a Linnei Species plantarum: exhibentes plantas rite cognitas, ad genera relatas, cum differentiis specificis, nominibus trivialibus, synonymis selectis, locis natalibus, secundum systema sexuale digestas, 3 (1). Impensis G. C. Nauk, Berolini, pp. 375 - 380." type="book chapter" year="1800">Willdenow (1800)</bibRefCitation>
published 
<taxonomicName id="4C212FF00723A23B5168EA0FFD8E4C55" authorityName="Willdenow" authorityYear="1800" box="[562,687,843,868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="strigosa">
<emphasis id="B95588610723A23B5168EA0FFD8E4C55" box="[562,687,843,868]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">B. strigosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a diagnostic phrase name “ 
<emphasis id="B95588610723A23B576EEA0FFD574CB9" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">
<taxonomicName id="4C212FF00723A23B576EEA0FFB864C55" box="[1076,1191,843,868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inermis">B inermis</taxonomicName>
, foliis oblongis subtus petiolis ramisque strigosis, bracteis ciliatis
</emphasis>
” and provided its origin as “Habitat in 
<collectingCountry id="F33614E30723A23B571CEA2AFBA14CB9" box="[1094,1152,878,904]" name="India" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">India</collectingCountry>
orientali” and “v.s.” (vidi siccas), indicating that he had seen at least one herbarium specimen. 
<location id="8EFE02A80723A23B50D8EAD6FCE24C9D" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0388E5650723A23B53D2E885FD454969:8EFE02A80723A23B50D8EAD6FCE24C9D" box="[898,963,914,940]" country="India" name="There" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">There</location>
are 
<specimenCount id="9D279FFA0723A23B50A8EAD7FBB64C9D" box="[1010,1175,914,941]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
in B-W (B-W 11664 -01 0 and B-W 11664 -02 0). Both specimens are in good condition bearing leaves, inflorescence and flowers. Willdenow’s protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="4C212FF00723A23B527EEA9FFEBA4CC5" authorityName="Willdenow" authorityYear="1800" box="[292,411,987,1012]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="strigosa">
<emphasis id="B95588610723A23B527EEA9FFEBA4CC5" box="[292,411,987,1012]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">B. strigosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
matches with the morphology of both specimens and they can be considered original material. Here, we designate the specimen (B-W 11664 -02 0) as 
<typeStatus id="549AEAD10723A23B504FEABAFC5E4B29" box="[789,895,1022,1048]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">lectotype</typeStatus>
, which is well mounted on herbarium sheet and depicts flower structure clearly. 
<collectorName id="26D431A50723A23B52AFED66FD444B0D" box="[501,613,1058,1084]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">Curiously</collectorName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB029820723A23B512BED66FCF74B0D" author="Shendage, S. M. &amp; Yadav, S. R." box="[625,982,1058,1084]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" pagination="81 - 130" refId="ref4246" refString="Shendage, S. M. &amp; Yadav, S. R. (2010) Revision of the genus Barleria (Acanthaceae) in India. Rheedea 20: 81 - 130." type="journal article" year="2010">Shendage &amp; Yadav (2010: 107)</bibRefCitation>
indicated “Wall., Numer. List No. 
<quantity id="4CD9F9960723A23B563FED66FA8A4B0C" box="[1381,1451,1058,1085]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.509" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" unit="g" value="2509.0">2509g</quantity>
(CAL)” as “type”, but this gathering, from cultivation in the 
<collectorName id="26D431A50723A23B5078ED02FB164B51" box="[802,1079,1094,1120]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">Calcutta Botanic Garden</collectorName>
, was almost certainly unavailable to 
<collectorName id="26D431A50723A23B53FEED2EFE3E4BB5" box="[164,287,1130,1156]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">Willdenow</collectorName>
in 1800.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9E54730723A23B53E7EDCAFE4A4AB1" blockId="8.[136,1452,842,1625]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">
Wallich (1830) described 
<taxonomicName id="4C212FF00723A23B52BDEDCBFD5D4B99" authorityName="Wallich" authorityYear="1830" box="[487,636,1166,1192]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="polytricha">
<emphasis id="B95588610723A23B52BDEDCBFD5D4B99" box="[487,636,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">B. polytricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on 
<specimenCount id="9D279FFA0723A23B51AFEDCBFCA14B98" box="[757,896,1167,1193]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" type="generic" typeStatus="syntype">two syntype</specimenCount>
gatherings, one raised in the 
<location id="8EFE02A80723A23B5783EDCAFFFB4BFD" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0388E5650723A23B53D2E885FD454969:8EFE02A80723A23B5783EDCAFFFB4BFD" country="Myanmar" county="Wallich's Catalogue" municipality="Here" name="Calcutta Botanical Garden" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" stateProvince="Ayeyawady">Calcutta Botanical Garden</location>
from seed he collected below 
<location id="8EFE02A80723A23B5112EDF7FDB04BFC" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0388E5650723A23B53D2E885FD454969:8EFE02A80723A23B5112EDF7FDB04BFC" box="[584,657,1203,1229]" country="Myanmar" county="Wallich's Catalogue" municipality="Here" name="Prome" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" stateProvince="Ayeyawady">Prome</location>
along the 
<location id="8EFE02A80723A23B5048EDF6FC574BFD" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0388E5650723A23B53D2E885FD454969:8EFE02A80723A23B5048EDF6FC574BFD" box="[786,886,1202,1228]" country="Myanmar" county="Wallich's Catalogue" municipality="Here" name="Irawaddi" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" stateProvince="Ayeyawady">Irawaddi</location>
[
<collectingRegion id="49E59A910723A23B50DCEDF6FB384BFC" box="[902,1049,1202,1229]" country="Myanmar" name="Ayeyawady" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">Ayeyarwady</collectingRegion>
] 
<location id="8EFE02A80723A23B5770EDF6FB494BFD" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0388E5650723A23B53D2E885FD454969:8EFE02A80723A23B5770EDF6FB494BFD" box="[1066,1128,1202,1228]" country="Myanmar" county="Wallich's Catalogue" municipality="Here" name="River" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" stateProvince="Ayeyawady">River</location>
(Wallich’s Cat. no. 7143A: K001126778) and another collected by 
<location id="8EFE02A80723A23B5115ED92FC534BC0" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0388E5650723A23B53D2E885FD454969:8EFE02A80723A23B5115ED92FC534BC0" box="[591,882,1238,1265]" country="Myanmar" county="Wallich's Catalogue" municipality="Here" name="William Gomez in Tavoy" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" stateProvince="Ayeyawady">William Gomez in Tavoy</location>
(Wallich’s Cat. no. 7143B: K001126779). 
<collectorName id="26D431A50723A23B5638ED92FA8A4BC0" box="[1378,1451,1238,1265]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">The K</collectorName>
specimen of 7143A bears an original label indicating 
<location id="8EFE02A80723A23B51BFEDBFFC604A24" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0388E5650723A23B53D2E885FD454969:8EFE02A80723A23B51BFEDBFFC604A24" box="[741,833,1275,1301]" country="Myanmar" county="Wallich's Catalogue" municipality="Here" name="Meaong" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" stateProvince="Ayeyawady">Meaong</location>
(now 
<collectingCountry id="F33614E30723A23B50D0EDBFFCDA4A24" box="[906,1019,1275,1301]" name="Myanmar" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
), whereas that of 7143B lacks locality information. 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BFACE090723A23B5247EC5BFE774A08" box="[285,342,1311,1337]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">Here</collectingMunicipality>
, we designate the specimen bearing 
<collectingCounty id="62FF2CFF0723A23B51A5EC5AFCC54A09" box="[767,996,1310,1336]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">Wallich’s Catalogue</collectingCounty>
no. 7143A (K001126778) as 
<typeStatus id="549AEAD10723A23B5664EC5AFA894A09" box="[1342,1448,1310,1336]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">lectotype</typeStatus>
. 
<collectorName id="26D431A50723A23B53D2EC06FFEE4A6D" box="[136,207,1346,1372]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">Again</collectorName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB029820723A23B5387EC06FD674A6D" author="Shendage, S. M. &amp; Yadav, S. R." box="[221,582,1346,1372]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" pagination="81 - 130" refId="ref4246" refString="Shendage, S. M. &amp; Yadav, S. R. (2010) Revision of the genus Barleria (Acanthaceae) in India. Rheedea 20: 81 - 130." type="journal article" year="2010">Shendage &amp; Yadav (2010: 107)</bibRefCitation>
indicated “Wall., Numer. List No. 7143a (CAL)” as “type”, but this has no standing (
<collectorName id="26D431A50723A23B53ACEC22FE054AB1" box="[246,292,1382,1408]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">Art.</collectorName>
7.11).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9E54730723A23B53E7ECCFFD454969" blockId="8.[136,1452,842,1625]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">
<bibRefCitation id="EFB029820723A23B53E7ECCFFE674A95" author="Nees Von Esenbeck, C. G." box="[189,326,1418,1445]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" pagination="91 - 93" refId="ref3929" refString="Nees Von Esenbeck, C. G. (1832) Acanthaceae Indiae Orientalis. In: N. Wallich (Ed.) Plantae Asiaticae rariores, or, Descriptions and figures of a select number of unpublished East Indian plants, 3. Treuttel et Wurtz, London, pp. 91 - 93." type="book chapter" year="1832">Nees (1832)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C212FF00723A23B52E4ECCFFD0A4A95" authorityName="Nees" authorityYear="1832" box="[446,555,1418,1444]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<emphasis id="B95588610723A23B52E4ECCFFD0A4A95" box="[446,555,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">B. hirsuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on 
<specimenCount id="9D279FFA0723A23B51C0ECCFFC004A94" box="[666,801,1419,1445]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" type="generic" typeStatus="syntype">two syntype</specimenCount>
gatherings, one from Prome and another from Tong Dong, both from 
<collectingCountry id="F33614E30723A23B5259ECEBFE534AF8" box="[259,370,1455,1481]" name="Myanmar" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
. We found that the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C212FF00723A23B51C3ECEBFC664AF8" authority="Nees" authorityName="Nees" authorityYear="1832" box="[665,839,1454,1481]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<emphasis id="B95588610723A23B51C3ECEBFC264AF9" box="[665,775,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">B. hirsuta</emphasis>
Nees
</taxonomicName>
is a later homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C212FF00723A23B570CECEBFA244AF8" authority="Jacq." authorityName="Jacq." box="[1110,1285,1454,1481]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<emphasis id="B95588610723A23B570CECEBFBE54AF9" box="[1110,1220,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">B. hirsuta</emphasis>
Jacq.
</taxonomicName>
and hence, an illegitimate name. In search of the original material, we found 
<specimenCount id="9D279FFA0723A23B5061EC96FCCF4ADD" box="[827,1006,1490,1516]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
collected by 
<collectorName id="26D431A50723A23B57DAEC96FA354ADC" box="[1152,1300,1490,1517]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">Wallich. Two</collectorName>
are housed at K, i.e. from 
<collectorName id="26D431A50723A23B524FECB3FE7F4920" box="[277,350,1527,1553]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">Prome</collectorName>
(Wallich’s Cat. no. 7142A: K001126776) and 
<collectorName id="26D431A50723A23B5007ECB3FCF84920" box="[861,985,1527,1553]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">Tong Dong</collectorName>
(Wallich’s Cat. no. 7142B: K001126777). 
<collectorName id="26D431A50723A23B53D2EF5EFF954905" box="[136,180,1562,1588]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">The</collectorName>
third one from 
<collectorName id="26D431A50723A23B5231EF5FFEDB4904" box="[363,506,1563,1589]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">Prome Mont</collectorName>
is at GZU (Wallich’s no. 130: GZU000249406). 
<collectorName id="26D431A50723A23B5768EF5FFB4A4904" box="[1074,1131,1563,1589]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">Here</collectorName>
, we designate the specimen from GZU (GZU000249406) as 
<typeStatus id="549AEAD10723A23B52ACEF7AFD414969" box="[502,608,1598,1624]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
